The paper presents a large-scale dataset for image classification, object detection, and visual relationship detection, which are all subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the performance of modern models, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for visual relationship detection, which could be relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Flickr as a source for the dataset, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
